# Code owners — GitHub auto-requests review from the listed
# handles when a PR touches a matching path.
#
# Single maintainer today. As the project grows, this file gets
# split per tier — Tier-1 (`crates/core/`) needs the tightest
# review bar per CLAUDE.md and would carry a separate owner team
# once one exists.
#
# Syntax: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-customizations/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Catch-all: every PR pings the maintainer for review.
*  @algedonic-dev/maintainers

# Hot paths that especially benefit from a flag-down review:
# audit_log + projection rebuilders + posting rules are the
# correctness backbone; bypassing them is the most common way
# to break the five-property contract.
/crates/core/boss-events/        @algedonic-dev/maintainers
/crates/core/boss-jobs/          @algedonic-dev/maintainers
/crates/core/boss-policy/        @algedonic-dev/maintainers
/crates/modules/boss-ledger/     @algedonic-dev/maintainers
/infra/postgres/schema.sql       @algedonic-dev/maintainers
/docs/adr/                       @algedonic-dev/maintainers
/docs/design/correctness-protocol.md  @algedonic-dev/maintainers
